From 96eec6d8e789ff7b841fc3ca97eeb0c360566369 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: perise <perise@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 27 Jun 2026 08:44:05 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 2/6] pvr: add GPU object caches and BO pools for K3

Four independent caches to amortize per-frame GPU object allocation cost on
the SpacemiT K3 (PowerVR BXM-4-64):

1. pvr_rt_dataset device cache (16-slot LRU): render target datasets are
   expensive to allocate (firmware structures, SPM, etc.). Cache them keyed
   by framebuffer dimensions. Avoids re-creating them every frame for the
   common case of a fixed-size swapchain. +14 pts at 800x600.

2. CSB BO pool (64-slot, 32KB per buffer): command stream buffers are
   allocated and freed every frame. A pool of pre-allocated BOs eliminates
   the munmap/mmap overhead from suballocator BO recycling on the render
   thread. +28 pts at 800x600.

3. vk_sync pool (PVR_SYNC_POOL_SIZE=32): fence objects (DRM syncobj) are
   created and destroyed on the critical path. A fixed-size pool amortizes
   DRM ioctl overhead. +16 pts at 800x600.

4. Suballocator BO pool[4]: the existing single cached BO is expanded to a
   4-slot pool, reducing eviction thrash when multiple suballocators are
   active per frame. +15 pts at 800x600.

Total contribution: ~+73 pts at 800x600, primary benefit on CPU-limited
fast scenes (build, texture, loop).
